parts.text: The old lighthouse keeper squinted at the encroaching fog. He'd seen countless storms, but this one felt different. A low, guttural moan echoed from the sea. Then, a figure emerged from the mist, its eyes glowing with an unnatural light. The keeper fumbled for his lantern, his heart pounding a frantic rhythm against his ribs. He knew, with chilling certainty, that this was no ordinary sailor lost at sea.
